  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Start your day with a sumptuous breakfast buffet of breads and baked goods, local cheeses, fresh fruit, fried eggs and more - all enjoyed with a spectacular alpine view. There's a selection of dairy-free and gluten-free products, too.</p>
<p>If you book Half Board, in the evening, you'll enjoy an excellent four-course evening meal with choice of dishes. Alternatively, book Bed and Breakfast and explore some of Wengen's lovely restaurants or book an evening in the Fondue Gondola for two. After dinner, the hotel bar is a great place to relax with an evening drink - there's snug seating, good music and an interesting menu of cocktails, refreshing long drinks and outstanding wine.</p>
<p>The <strong>Grill</strong><strong> Kota </strong>is a wooden grill-hut in the garden that can seat eight - 12 people. With a fireplace in the centre, it's the ideal place for a raclette or fondue evening with friends or family (the Grill Kota is payable locally, minimum eight people).</p>
<p>Book the <strong>Fondue Gondola </strong>for two people for the ultimate romantic evening. It's a two-seater, traditional gondola in the garden and is perfect for a unique evening (the Fondue Gondola is payable locally).</p>]]></cateringDescription>
