  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Rooms</strong> are around 17m² and sleep two people (twin or double bed). They have an ensuite with bath or shower. These rooms are available for sole occupancy for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Classic Rooms</strong> are around 20m² and sleep two people (twin or double bed). They have an ensuite with bath or shower. These rooms are available for sole occupancy for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege Rooms</strong> are around 26m² and sleep two people (twin or double bed). They have a lounge area and an ensuite with bath or shower.</p>
<p><strong>Duplex Family Rooms</strong> are around 35m² and sleep three to four people (twin or double bed, plus bunk bed). They are over two levels with an open-plan layout, lounge area and ensuite with bath.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Village view</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Tea/coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. CHF5.30 per person per night is payable locally. Children aged between six and 15 have a reduced fee of CHF2.00 per person per night. Children aged five years and under are exempt.</p>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>4pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
